    <thetext>The 4.11 kernels are likely to cause issues on certain Intel SSDs when used with (I think) to Kaby Lake hosts.  Insufficiently tested fix here:

https://lkml.kernel.org/r/db392f7634625bea0ede96c119b500d16ba9e9db.1495663545.git.luto@kernel.org

FWIW, those same SSDs are apparently already highly problematic when running XFS on all hosts, but the new regression affects them regardless of filesystem.</thetext>
